modules.description: Returns the domain of a number as a pair of its lower and upper bounds. Computes the greatest common divisor of two numbers using a specialized algorithm. Designed for numerical analysis and mathematical computations requiring precision.

Provides operations for manipulating logical expressions, including substitution, simplification, and theorem proving. Works with abstract syntax trees representing mathematical formulas and proof states. Used to automate deductions in formal verification tasks and symbolic computation.

Provides functions to load and manage HOL theory files, including expanding directories, checking file presence on paths, and tracking loaded files with their digests. Operates with strings, lists of strings, and digest values to ensure correct file handling and avoid re-loading. Used to dynamically load dependencies and manage the HOL environment during theorem proving sessions.

Calculates numerical domains and computes greatest common divisors with precision. It handles arbitrary-precision integers through operations like bound extraction and GCD calculation. Users can determine value ranges and perform exact arithmetic on large numbers. This enables accurate mathematical analysis and algorithmic implementations requiring exact results.
